      <div class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">ü•Ñ Steps to Prepare</h2>
        <ol class="list-decimal list-inside text-gray-600 space-y-4">
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold">Make the Dressing:</span>
            <p>Whisk together white vinegar, fish sauce, sugar, lime juice, minced garlic, and red pepper flakes in a small bowl. Set aside.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold">Caramelize the Shallots:</span>
            <p>Heat canola oil in a skillet over medium heat. Add chopped shallots and cook until softened and lightly caramelized, about 8 minutes. Set aside.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold">Grill the Shrimp:</span>
            <p>Preheat an outdoor grill to medium heat and lightly oil the grate. Skewer the shrimp and grill for 1‚Äì2 minutes per side, or until pink and slightly charred. Set aside.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold">Cook the Noodles:</span>
            <p>Bring a large pot of water to a boil. Add rice vermicelli noodles and cook for 12 minutes, or until softened. Drain and rinse with cold water, separating the noodles as needed.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold">Assemble the Bowls:</span>
            <p>Divide cooked noodles between two serving bowls. Arrange lettuce, bean sprouts, cucumber matchsticks, pickled carrots, daikon radish, crushed peanuts, cilantro, Thai basil, mint, and caramelized shallots on top. Serve with grilled shrimp skewers and the dressing on the side. Toss thoroughly before eating.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </div>

